
[1]heathful

   HEATH'FUL, a. helth'ful. Being in a sound state, as a living or
   organized being; having the parts or organs entire,and their functions
   in a free, active and undisturbed operation; free from disease. We
   speak of a healthful body, a healthful person, a healthful plant.

   1. Serving to promote health; wholesome; salubrious; as a healthful air
   or climate; a healthful diet.

   2. Indicating health or soundness; as a healthful condition.

   3. Salutary; promoting spiritual health.

   4. Well disposed; favorable.

   A healthful ear to hear. [Unusual.]
